_refine.details                                  
;RESIDUES 162 - 164 IN WILD-TYPE AND ALL MUTANT LYSOZYMES
ARE EXTREMELY MOBILE.  THUS THE COORDINATES FOR THESE
RESIDUES ARE VERY UNRELIABLE.

THE SIDE CHAINS OF RESIDUES 8, 14, 16, 80, 83, 119, AND 162
HAVE WEAK DENSITY AND PROBABLY ARE IN MULTIPLE
CONFORMATIONS OR COMPLETELY DISORDERED.  THE COORDINATES
REPRESENT THE BEST REFINED FIT TO THE OBSERVED 2F0-FC
DENSITY.
;
